=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_FBSineC_ex5 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright mixed sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 459 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 459.4793
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.6160
  harmonic_regularity: 0.4682
  pitch_clarity: 51.3947
  inharmonicity: 0.6429
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -29.0981
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: FBSineC Example 5
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/FBSineC.html
// Tags: FBSineC, Classes, oscillator
// ---
// --- Example 5 ---
// modulate frequency and index multiplier
{ FBSineC.ar(LFNoise2.kr(1, 1e4, 1e4), LFNoise2.kr(1, 16, 17), 1, 1.005, 0.7) * 0.2 }.play(s);
